# Terminal Usage Guidelines

## Overview
This document provides guidelines for efficient and safe usage of terminal commands within the Cursor development workflow.

## Best Practices
- Always run commands within the appropriate virtual environment.
- Avoid using destructive operations without proper approval.
- Log important outputs and errors for troubleshooting.
- Verify command context (current directory, permissions) before execution.

## Command Execution Guidelines
- Follow repository conventions for executing terminal commands.
- Validate multi-line commands using scripts.
- Ensure terminal output is reviewed for any errors. 